Text.Value: Swell with pride.
*With a hiccough, you discover him to be drunk yet again from imbibing the tonsil stone pickling water.*
*With a start, a moment floods back - the gaping knife-hole in your brain seems to have briefly knitted together.*
*As you snaffle the pungent mushroom, a lone memory unfolds in your rancid cortex.*
Wonder who you were, before you were drawn to Bhaal's Temple.
Mourn: why did that sweet child have to suffer so?
*Foster parents who cared for a lost Bhaalspawn? Dreams of your own future, before the awakening of the Urge?*
Hold the trembling artery closed with your bare fist, dissecting onwards with the other.
Delve: why did it die?
Shudder. Might that family have taken you in?
*The mangled meat-pile Orin turned your brain to at last deigns to send you a memory.*
Wince: you wish to remember no further.
*With a start, the spell knits your mind together - just about long enough for you to recall a single image.*
*Waah! Waah! Boo hoo hoo!*

EditorData.NodeContext: Baby crying effect/imitation, meant to mock the Dark Urge for trying to forget themselves.

Text.Value: *The memory fades... and you are left alone.*
*Words creep from the darkness...*
*A little Urge - not even an adolescent - stands with a tiny dagger atop a bloody heap.*
*A study no doubt arranged neatly by your gentleman's gentlegoblin.*
Sneer. A pathetic first outing.
*Better to die than live on an earth walked by you. Each of your deaths is a mercy.*
*Play. Friends. Fun. A time before Bhaal. *
*Mayhaps that child was already a murderer.*
*As you choke down the acrid mushroom, a memory hounds you.*
*As the memory begins to clears away, one thing is certain: the Butler lies not about his past service.*
Drown the Butler in the victim's open bladder-cavity.
*A babe. Brained by your hand.*
Salivate: the carcass would make four dishes of excellent nutritive meat.
Scream: 'Useless Butler!'
*As you and your Butler perform a vivisection, Sceleritas' claw slips, calipers cutting the aorta of the living, screaming victim...*
Ignore the memory: You've won, your own life is back.
*The fore or hind quarter will make a reasonable dish, and seasoned with a little pepper or salt, will be very good boiled on the fourth day. Especially in winter.*
*Freedom. Friends. Life. A time after Bhaal.*
*As you choke down the acrid mushroom, a memory embraces your unlovable carcass.*
*How many loved ones died?*
*His tears mingle in with the golden fountain.*
*You see a grand collection: shelves of jarred floating pickled organs neatly labelled. Taxidermied beasts and men, elegantly displayed from your killings.*
*Children darting their way through the city streets of the Gate, chasing one another. While you hunt like a lion, your tag touch is gentle.*
*Two-bedroom cottage. Relative squalor. Poor part of the city. Indiscriminate whole-family kill. Baby's first murder spree.*
Young Master, precious fledgling, follow ever your heart. In time, your true family will find you.
*This is not your first time unravelling a long intestine left-handed, but each time you swear up a storm, hoping it will be your last.*

Synopsis:
The Dark Urge is subject to a powerful healing spell (Heal) and recovers some lost memories.

This is just the Dark Urge being told by the narrator about their past.
